haxe.FastList<T>

type
class
A linked-list of elements. A different class is created for each container used in platforms where it matters

Constructor

new()
Creates a new empty list.

Instance Variables

head : FastCell<T>

Instance Methods

inline add(item : T) : Void

Add an element at the head of the list.

inline first() : Null<T>

Returns the first element of the list, or null if the list is empty.

inline isEmpty() : Bool

Tells if a list is empty.

iterator() : Iterator<T>

Returns an iterator on the elements of the list.

inline pop() : Null<T>

Removes the first element of the list and returns it or simply returns null if the list is empty.

remove(v : T) : Bool

Remove the first element that is == v from the list. Returns true if an element was removed, false otherwise.

toString() : String

Returns a displayable representation of the String.
